Step 1. Calculate Debt to Equity Ratio  
• From the balance sheet, the components are:  
 – Total Liabilities = Total Liabilities and Owner’s Equity – Total Owner’s Equity  
  = 14,930,535.06 – 13,963,263.19 = 967,271.87  
 – Total Owner’s Equity = 13,963,263.19  
• Therefore, Debt to Equity Ratio = 967,271.87 / 13,963,263.19 ≈ 0.0693 → 0.07

Step 2. Calculate Net Profit Margin  
• From the income statement:  
 – Net Profit = 963,263.19  
 – Total Revenue = 3,025,437.82  
• Net Profit Margin = (963,263.19 / 3,025,437.82) × 100% ≈ 31.83%

Step 3. Calculate Return on Assets (ROA)  
• From the balance sheet:  
 – Total Assets = 14,930,535.06  
• ROA = (963,263.19 / 14,930,535.06) × 100% ≈ 6.45%

Step 4. Calculate Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
• For turnover ratio, we use Revenue divided by Average Accounts Receivable.  
• Accounts Receivable on the balance sheet:  
 – Beginning Accounts Receivable (2023-12-31) = 0.00  
 – Ending Accounts Receivable (2024-02-05) = 1,716,911.17  
 – Average Accounts Receivable = (0 + 1,716,911.17) / 2 = 858,455.585  
• Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = 3,025,437.82 / 858,455.585 ≈ 3.525, or about 3.53

Thus, the solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.07",
    "Net Profit Margin": "31.83%",
    "Return on Assets (ROA)": "6.45%",
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "3.53"
  }
}
